H0.text: Individuals are the number counted in population size in a population.

H1.text: Humans are the number counted in the population size of a population.

H2.text: Subdivisions are the number that constitutes the population size in a population.

H3.text: Proteins are the number that makes up the population size in a population.

A4.text: population size (usually denoted N) is a countable quantity representing the number of individual organisms in a population.
